Live blog and updates: Two Iraqis fightback after Donald Trump issues temporary immigration ban Live blog and updates: Two Iraqis fightback after Donald Trump issues temporary immigration ban A US judge blocked the deportation of travelers and refugees from seven Muslim-majority nations who are at US airports under. By: FE Online | New Delhi | Published: January 29, 2017 10:29 AM Protests against Donald Trump continues. (Reuters) 
10.21 AM: A US judge blocked the deportation of travelers and refugees from seven Muslim-majority nations who are at US airports under. This was done after a case was filed on behalf of two Iraqis who have ties to US security forces.
